requires: [FRONTEND_DEV, ARCHITECT]

###############################################################################
# REQUIREMENTS
###############################################################################
requirements:
  - Remove from navitrack-apps/draft/pwa-react-app-clear/src/styles/app-layout.css the block at lines 115–124 (`.main-scroll-content:not(.main-scroll-content--map)`, `.main-scroll-content.main-scroll-content--map`, `.main-scroll-content p`).
  - Move min-height and padding responsibility to layout layer (e.g. Main.tsx or a dedicated layout/content class in a layout-scoped stylesheet) so content area rules are not in app-layout.css.
  - Preserve behavior: non-map screens have minimum height and padding; map screen has padding 0.

###############################################################################
# DELIVERABLES
###############################################################################
deliverables:
  - app-layout.css without the content-specific block at 115–124.
  - Layout component or layout CSS that owns content min-height and padding.

###############################################################################
# INSTRUCTIONS
###############################################################################
instructions:
  1. Edit app-layout.css: delete the .main-scroll-content rules (min-height, padding, p margin).
  2. Add equivalent rules to Main.tsx classNames or to a layout-specific CSS file imported by layout only.
  3. Verify build and that map vs non-map content still render correctly.
